A component class PRODUCES components aka, the instance is a component

USAGE:
------
class NewComponent extends React.Component {
    constructor(props) {
        <initialize method>
    }
    newFxn (<vars>) {
        <code ...>
    }

    render() {
        <logic_here> // dont put it above the render....

        return (
            <p 
                onClick={this.newFxn}>
                paragraph text
            </p>)
    }
}

ReactDOM.render(
    <NewComponent />,
    document.getElementById('ID')
)


React.Component is a js class, thus to reate a new one, you must subclass it 
write them in ES2015 not arrow fxns
components are <Capitalized />
calling methods or event handlers in the render need to use THIS